===Etymology===
Law {{L.}} [[present]] [[passive]] [[infinitive]] of ''[[certioro]]'', a contraction of ''[[certiorem facere]]'' ("to [[search]]", literally "to [[make]] [[certain]]").

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|-}}
# {{US}} {{law}} A grant of the right of an [[appeal]] to be heard by an [[appellate]] [[court]] where that court has [[discretion]] to choose which appeals it will hear.
# {{UK}} {{law}} A grant of review of a [[government]] action by a court with discretion to make such a review.

